I put a @boba on our baby registry as soon as I found out I was pregnant. There are so many great benefits to baby wearing and while there are tons of different options (wraps, slings, carriers, backpacks, etc)… I felt like the Boba Wrap was ideal for my lifestyle in these past couple of months. I’ll share a more in depth review in my blog next week but here are a few pros and cons to the Boba that I’ve experienced so far:

Pros-
• it’s very comfortable to wear. No buckles or rings pinching me on my side. All fabric with a snug fit for baby and me
• Free hands! Having to carry a baby while also handling a toddler and every day activities (dishes, laundry, etc) can be difficult but baby wearing is so convenient. I put River in my @boba and I’m able to get so much done. 
• I felt confident going to more places with my baby! I’ve brought her to many outings because of it (even Mardi Gras!). Having her so close to mommy makes her feel safe and warm. It always makes her calm!
• Built in privacy for breastfeeding plus EASY access! 

Cons- specifically for the Boba: 
• it IS a lot of fabric which makes the wrapping part a little tricky getting used to. 
• I had River in the Winter. The added warmth was great in the cooler months. But Summer is here and not gonna lie… it’s getting a little hot in there 

Cons for baby wearing in general:
• yes, breastfeeding is convenient… but if you’re not wearing a top with easy access to the boob, you’re fried 😵‍💫
• in the event of a poop explosion while baby wearing, you’ll also be wearing that poop 🙃

In general, if River is fussy for whatever reason, I put her in the carrier and within minutes, we’re all good so I’d still highly recommend a baby carrier or any kind! It’s just about finding one that fits your style and needs!

Have you used a baby carrier for your littles? If so, let me know which one in a comment below. I’d love to read about your experience using one! And be on the look out for my full, in-depth review of the @boba on my blog next week! 
www.RocioIsabel.com

¡Que orgullo ser Latino! Seriously, it fills my heart with so much pride to feel connected to my roots and I can only hope that I can instill that pride and love for our culture in my own daughters. I mentioned recently how excited I am to be a #TargetPartner because Penelope loves @Target just as much as I do. How exciting is it, though, to be able to go shopping in our favorite place and find products from Latino Owned Brands where we can see ourselves represented in what we bring home from the store! 

I wanted to teach Penelope how to make tortillas FROM SCRATCH! You all should know by now how much P LOVES to help out in the kitchen. And since she has done so well as my sous chef in her lifetime, I thought now is the BEST time to show her what my own abuelita taught me. 

When I was about 4 or 5, mi abuelita taught me how to make tortillas from scratch using la plancha and comal. Of course, she never let me touch the comal, but she did teach me how to use the plancha and I have never forgotten that memory. I was starting to wonder if Penelope is too young to remember this later but the fact that I just had to show her how to use the plancha (tortilla presser) once makes me feel more confident that at least the steps are just natural to her because she is part Latina herself! 

Is there a recipe or dish your abuelita or mama taught you that you have never forgotten? Something that gives you so much orgullo de ser Latino? Let me know what it is in the comment below. Y’all should know by now the next dish I want to teach Penelope how to make… Baleadas! 

Check out my stories! I’m sharing all links to the products we used to make our tortillas from scratch. From the harina to the plancha, comal, and more! #MasQue #UnidosUnicos #Target

It’s official, Summer is here. I mean, It’s felt like summer for the last 4 months but I digress 😅 Penelope is off to water day and lance and I are frantically packing for our first trip as a family of 4. River is just cool as a cucumber minding her own (until she’s hungry, they she loses her caca). 

Man I need this vacation.
But them I’m pretty sure I’ll need a vacation from this vacation. 🙃

We survived our first vacation as a family of 4! 😭😅 granted, our destination was met with more family members… but we survived nonetheless! Every year, we go on a big family vacation, a “Mora Reunion” with my parents and siblings! This year’s vacation was a trip to Orlando and I just want to start off by saying - LAWD IT WAS HOT! 🥵 I don’t think it was as hot as New Orleans BUT spending most of our time outside managing moments with the girls was overall stressful and HOT! We were still able to make great memories though, thanks to @mazdausa for keeping us cool along the way! Hello cooling seats 🥰🙌🏽 

While we’re used to spending family vacations together and doing everything with everyone, we learned very quickly that life with kids changes things. It’s not a bad thing, but you learn to adjust and make the most out of unexpected plans. Ask me how many times we’ve been held back because of poop 💩🙃 or how many times we were overwhelmed because of crying or tantrums. Lance and I both agree that this vacation flew by in a heartbeat! 

But no matter how stressed we were, as long as P and Riv we’re having fun, that’s all that mattered! 

Now, time to plan my vacation from my vacation 🤣😅😭

Who knew that I would find so much peace finally embracing my Señora Era. I mean, honestly… even before I got married, the thought of becoming a “Señora” made me feel a little weird. A U G U S T 🤎

Last month I spent a lot of my time thinking about what I wanted the rest of my year to look like. I took a bit of a step back these last couple of weeks focusing on my health (mental and physical). Between listening to a few “self help” podcasts and chatting with close friends, I realize that there are a lot of things I want differently in life than I did when I first started YouTube and this whole blogging/creator journey. 

For starters, I want to be more intentional with my time (and the time that those close to me choose to give). I need to prioritize self-care. I cannot pour from an empty cup. And I believe that putting myself first will allow me to be the best version of myself for those around me. 

I don’t want my girls to look back at photos and videos of me and think “man… mommy looks tired”. I want them to see a mommy that’s fulfilled. That is content. That is at peace. 

That’s up to me.

As far as work goes, I need to push myself to stay consistent. I feel like I’ve said that far too often in these 7 years, but my slow growth in the online world is nobody’s fault but my own. It effects my motivation, my relationship with those following me, the algorithm, and my opportunities to work with brands (which, transparently… effects what I bring home because this is my full time job). Then again, if I prioritize my mental health, I think it would be easier for me to stay consistent. I mean, It’s hard to put makeup on and fix my hair and smile for the camera when I’m not in the right head space. 

There’s more weighing on my mind, but wanted to share this as an extension of my Mami’s Exagerada List. Let’s revisit at the end of the month and I’ll let you know August really went down. 

Any personal goals you have for this month? 🤎

#augustgoals #personalgoals #august

We recently went on a family trip to Orlando, FL and Penelope had the BEST TIME by far at The Crayola Experience @visitcrayolaorl! It wasn’t on our itinerary originally and on the day we flew back home, we had several hours to find something to do. This place came highly rated and I’m so glad we made the decision to visit because we spent the WHOLE AFTERNOON there because there was so much to do! 

Seriously, this reel doesn’t even show half of what we did! There were more than 30 hands on activities to keep the little one (and adults) entertained! It’s located in the Florida Mall and entry is priced at $19.99 per person (free for kids 3 and under), and it takes about 4-5 hours to go through if you do every single activity! 

We named and wrapped our own crayon, were the stars of our very own coloring page, created spin art and our very own emoji crayon. 

There’s a giant kids play area, and smaller toddler play area on the other side of the snack center. If you’re really hungry, you can visit the Cafe for pizzas, chicken tenders, salads and more!

HIGHLY recommend this place as a MUST DO attraction in Orlando!

I’ve got a curious 3 year old that asks a lot of questions. Recently, she saw the mail carrier drive down our street and asked what was in their mail truck, what they put in our mailbox, why the mailbox has a flag, and why we get so many letters.

I thought this would be a fun way to answer all of her questions! 

On a recent trip to @visitcrayolaorl, we made our very own coloring sheets from photos taken of us! After a quick google search, I noticed that @crayola actually has an app that does this for you from your phone! 

Simply choose a photo from your phones photo album, make any adjustments you want, then save directly to your phone or print to a wireless printer straight from your phone! 

I love the idea of Penelope coloring special photos of people she loves, then mailing the pages to that special someone to let them know she’s thinking of them!

Now, Penelope knows what we use envelopes for, what postal stamps are used for, and how to use a mailbox! 

I give myself mommy bonus points if I can show her the mail carrier actually taking the letter from the mailbox and driving away! 🙌🏽

Don’t feel like mailing a letter? Just use the app to print your own coloring sheets with the photos from your phone! If your little one loves to color like Penelope does, I guarantee that will keep your little one occupied for hours!

Tag someone you think would find this video helpful!

Life as parents of two littles can be hard. Y’all really only see our highlights but we’ve had some tough times to navigate. A marriage can easily be tested daily with the additional roles and responsibilities of mom and dad. 

One thing I’ve learned is that strengthening your marriage should be priority. Because then your children will thrive in a home filled with love, honor, commitment, and security. 

It’s also easy to get lost in what feels like the routine of parenting. We’re in such a rush for the next milestone, for the kids to get older, for things to get “easier”. But I’m learning that being a parent never gets easier. Every day poses a new challenge that I need to navigate (and this is just the beginning. These are just the early years 😅). And now that we’re with baby 2, I’m realizing time is going even faster than when we had just 1. 

All we can do is take life one day at a time. And enjoy the time we have with each other. Because time changes ever so quickly and before you know it, these will be the days that we’ll want back.

Also, shoutout to @jesstress16, best wedding favors EVER!

#Ad I’ve really been enjoying the feeling I get when I cook dishes that connect me to my roots! Today, I’m igniting my Mexican palate and cooking one of my favorites - Tacos de Barbacoa. I kept thinking about the last time I visited family in Queretaro. It’s where I got my favorite apron! I wear this apron everytime I want to cook a latin dish, like my unofficial uniform.

Traditionally, barbacoa is cooked in a hole in the ground. Do you think this mama has the time or energy to do that? Absolutely not! That’s why I decided to turn to my trusty slow cooker! It’s been my saving grace on days when Mami’s Exagerada Lists get overwhelming.

Two meats that can be cooked to make Tacos de Barbacoa: @rumbameats Beef Cheek Meat or Beef Tongue. Today I made Tacos de barbacoa with Beef Cheek Meat and it was ABSOLUTELY DELICIOUS!

Here’s what you need:
About 5lbs of @rumbameats beef cheek meat

For Marinade:
6 dry guajillo chilis
1 dry ancho chili
1 dry pasilla chili
(optional for heat) 4 arbol chili
2 limes
4 garlic cloves
1 tsp dried Mexican oregano
1 tsp cumin
½ tsp whole black peppercorn
4 whole cloves
½ roughly cut onion
1 ½ cup of beef broth

For Tomatillo Salsa:
4-5 tomatillos
1 jalapeño
3 garlic cloves
½ white onion

Link in stories and bio to full recipe! 

Another recipe to wow Esposo with, and another recipe to pass down to my girls! Maybe next time, I’ll actually give Tacos de barbacoa especial a try, think #beyondtheplate and go for the tongue. But what about you? Have you ever had cheek meat or beef tongue before? Let me know in a comment below!

It’s the baby 😭🤢
You would think I know better now that I’m two kids in. Soiled diapers after introducing solids are on a whole other level. I thought I was safe with the Ubbi. I was convinced after having my first baby that it was the Diaper Genie. No friend, no matter the diaper pail, anything with a lid is free game with this ungodly odor. 

With our first baby, we threw out the diaper genie around 11 or so months. I remember well because it didn’t last til her first birthday. We switched to a regular trash can, put wet diapers in there and threw soiled diapers in the trash bin outside. 

River makes 10 months in a little over a week. I’ll be tossing the Ubbi at 10 months and we’ll be opting for a regular trash can again with same rules as before. Wet diapers in the trash can and soiled diapers in the bin outside.

Although, someone did have a clever tip with diaper pails. Throw the spiked diapers in a doggy bag and then throw it in the pail. 🤔 I’ll give it a try this week 🤣

As we continue to celebrate Hispanic Heritage Month, I wanted to share this delicious Hispanic recipe you can make in no time! With a change in the weather, I’ve been craving Tarta de Manzana (apple tart). One thing that reminds me of my Mexican Abuelita and her love for apples is this sweet dessert! 

So today I’m sharing the FASTEST way to this delicious treat! No oven necessary either! I baked this during my baby’s nap time so it’s Mami approved! But you can’t make this tarta de manzana without MANZANAS! So what better way to perfect this dish than with @envyapples that I picked up at @walmart! These apples are high quality and the slices stay naturally white for longer! You can add your apple slices in a beautiful pattern that will truly make this dessert stand out!

Ingredients:

•2 Envy Apples

•2 tablespoons of butter

•3 tablespoon of sugar for apples

•1/2 tablespoon of cinnamon

•the juice of 1/2 lemon

•3 eggs

•3 tablespoons of sugar for tart base

•3/4 cup of wheat flour

•1 tablespoon vanilla

• 1/2 tablespoon baking powder

Peel and slice Envy apples and add to a buttered pan on low heat. As apples soften, add sugar and cinnamon. As it caramelizes, add lemon juice. Position Envy apple slices in whatever pattern you like!

While apples soften, whisk eggs. When eggs begin to foam you know it’s the best consistency for your base! Add sugar, wheat flour, vanilla and baking powder and mix until smooth. 

GENTLY pour batter on top of the Envy apple slices (carefully not to move apples). Using a spatula, gently spread batter to cover and apples peeking through. Cover the pan and let cook for at least 10 minutes. 

After 10 minutes, check that the batter has hardened. Your tarta is ready when there are no sticky parts. Place a plate over the pan to “cover” then carefully yet quickly flip upside down to reveal your beautiful and delicious Tarta de Manzana!

Buen Provecho!

Let’s get vulnerable:
I haven’t been on a date with my husband in more than a year. Sure, we’ve been out… with friends… with family… with the girls… for work. But really, we’ve had one solo vacation. 

We sort of stopped… dating… each other. 😭

SOMEONE SOUND THE MARRIAGE ALARM!
🚨 🚨 🚨 🚨 

If I’m being honest, last year was ROUGH. Not so much mommyhood (if you leave out that postpartum panic attack that led me to the hospital). I’m talking more so about my self identity, and that of my love life. Today though, I want to talk about the love life and how having kids can seriously impact your marriage if you let it. 🙋🏽‍♀️ I was letting it 👀

I was wondering how much I wanted to share (and when) but I knew deep down that sharing was important because from private conversations I’ve had in the past 6 months or so, I’ve learned that what I was going through was far more common than people want to admit.

While raising a needy toddler AND an infant who was exclusively breastfeeding… I was touched TF out 😭 exhausted was an understatement. Overstimulated to say the least. Once the girls were out to sleep, I didn’t want anything or anyone to touch me in any way. 

Enter the love of my life. 

It’s one thing to have him to understand and respect where I was coming from when I would vocalize how exhausted and overstimulated I was at the end of the day… it’s another thing to completely dismiss his feelings of rejection. Resentment would creep in and I would let it get the best of me. 

I’m learning. 

I guess I feel comfortable sharing because as I have started weaning, I’ve felt more myself. I’ve felt more confident and comfortable with my body. I’m getting my groove back to put things mildly 😏 and as I’ve constantly been reminded… these kids ain’t gonna be around forever. 

It’s important to remember that dating your spouse doesn’t stop when you get married, and it shouldn’t stop when you have kids.

This year, Lance and I are committed to going on more dates, so I’ve put together a date for each letter of the alphabet to make planning a little easier (no excuses). Today, we picked M… Matinee Movie. 

Stick around to see what letter we pick next!

Wait for it… 🥹

First off, Penelope is a rock star in the making and her requests for The Black Keys make my heart dance! Lance and I have always had a sweet spot for @theblackkeys 🥹 

Like I had mentioned before, River had been taking a couple steps here and there. And the other day she made it from one side of the kitchen to the other with me resulting in tears because OH MY GOD MY BABY IS GROWING SO FAST 😭 of course, I didn’t get any of it on camera. 

Today, in the middle of Penelope’s concert debut, River danced her way down the living room. 

With The Black Keys, anything is possible.
